SIMPLE: money-making
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Money-making
<hw>Mon"ey-mak`ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act or process of making
money; the acquisition and accumulation of wealth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Obstinacy in <qex>money-making</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Money-making</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Money-making
<hw>Mon"ey-mak`ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Affording
profitable returns; lucrative; <as>as, a <ex>money-making</ex>
business</as>. Opposite of <contr>unprofitable</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Successful in gaining money, and devoted to that
aim; <as>as, a <ex>money-making</ex> man</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>moneyman</ent>⟦br⟧
